Reasoning: The paper discusses the topological structure of the World Wide Web and the challenges in understanding it. It also analyzes the statistical properties of different WWW graphs obtained through crawlers and discusses the issue of sampling biases. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the navigability and searchability of the Web, which falls under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper touches upon the issue of structural differences in Web crawls, which could be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
